ed%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Republic%20of%20India%E2%80%99%3F%20You%20are%20not%20representing%20the%20Union%20or%20the%20Republic.%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20represent%20the%20Union%20of%20India%3F%20You%20cannot%20file%20your%20petitions%20like%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fyou-cannot-call-yourself-republic-of-india-in-pleas-sc-pulls-up-cbi-101697823661572.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20A.S.%20Oka%20and%20Justice%20Pankaj%20Mithal%20as%20saying%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20reminded%20the%20CBI%20that%20its%20mandate%20under%20the%20law%20is%20to%20probe%20illegalities%20of%20both%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20an%20independent%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20remarks%2C%20the%20Bench%20ordered%20the%20cause-title%20of%20the%20case%20be%20altered%20by%20the%20court%20registry%2C%20omitting%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98Republic%20of%20India%E2%80%99.%20Additional%20solicitor%20general%20(ASG)%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20agreed%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20pertinent%20to%20recall%20that%20in%20November%202021%2C%20the%20West%20Bengal%20government%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20questioning%20the%20CBI%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%20to%20register%20first%20information%20reports%20(FIRs)%20and%20conduct%20investigations%20in%20states.%20Instead%20of%20making%20CBI%2C%20an%20autonomous%20agency%2C%20a%20party%20to%20the%20case%2C%20the%20West%20Bengal%20government%20made%20the%20Union%20government%20a%20party.%20The%20Union%20government%20then%20said%20that%20it%20has%20no%20power%20over%20the%20exercise%20of%20authority%20by%20an%20autonomous%20body%20like%20the%20CBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20information%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20website%20reveals%20that%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20cases%20where%20the%20CBI%20represented%20itself%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Republic%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20not%20as%20%E2%80%98CBI%E2%80%99%2C%20%3Cem%3EHT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20in%20question%20pertains%20to%20CBI%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20against%20bail%20granted%20to%20Subhra%20Kundu%2C%20a%20former%20actress%20and%20the%20wife%20of%20Gautam%20Kundu%20who%20runs%20a%20chit-fund%20company%20called%20Rose%20Valley.%20The%20company%20is%20accused%20of%20a%20multi-crore%20scam%20which%20is%20currently%20under%20investigation%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPegged%20at%20Rs%2017%2C000%20crore%2C%20the%20alleged%20scam%20is%20the%20biggest%20in%20the%20history%20of%20West%20Bengal.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20in%202014%20ordered%20the%20CBI%20to%20investigate%20the%20role%20of%20influential%20people%20involved%20in%20money%20laundering%20in%20the%20state.%20According%20to%20the%20probe%20agency%2C%20the%20chit-fund%20group%20had%20established%2027%20companies%2C%20of%20which%20only%2012%20were%20active.%20The%20group%20is%20accused%20of%20hoodwinking%20gullible%20investors%20by%20promising%20inflated%20returns%20on%20their%20investments%20between%208%25%20and%2027%25.%20Investigation%20is%20currently%20underway%20in%20both%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Odisha%20high%20court%20in%20August%202022%20granted%20bail%20to%20Subhra%20Kundu%2C%20which%20is%20being%20challenged%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697877079000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21134523%2FThe-Wire-46.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-objects-to-cbi-terming-itself-republic-of-india-in-pleas-reminds-agency-of-its-mandate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20reminded%20the%20CBI%20that%20its%20mandate%2C%20under%20the%20law%2C%20is%20to%20probe%20illegalities%20of%20both%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20an%20independent%20agency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2