ity.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHimachal%20Pradesh%20Legislative%20Assembly%20recently%20passed%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20Universities%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20Horticulture%20and%20Forestry%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023.%20The%20Bill%20amends%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20Universities%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20Horticulture%20and%20Forestry%20Act%2C%201986%2C%20under%20which%20two%20of%20the%20seven%20state%20universities%20are%20established%20and%20governed.%20The%20amended%20Sections%202%2C%2023%2C%20and%2024%20of%20the%20Act%20confer%20the%20exclusive%20power%20upon%20the%20governor%20of%20the%20state%20(in%20the%20ex-officio%20capacity%20of%20chancellor)%20to%20appoint%20vice-chancellors%20of%20Sarwan%20Kumar%20Krishi%20Vishvavidyalay%2C%20Palampur%2C%C2%A0and%20Dr.%20Y.S.%20Parmar%20University%20of%20Horticulture%20and%20Forestry%2C%20Solan%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Caid%20and%20advice%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20of%20objects%20and%20reasons%20of%20the%20Bill%20claim%20to%20pursue%20objectives%20of%20the%20National%20Education%20Policy%2C%202020%20and%20give%20effect%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Caspirations%20of%20the%20people%E2%80%9D.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20amendments%20are%20carried%20out%20to%20%E2%80%9Callow%20the%20Democratic%20Government%20to%20exercise%20its%20right%20to%20shape%20the%20institutions%20of%20higher%20learning%20by%20exclusively%20controlling%20the%20appointment%20of%20VCs%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Amendment%20abolishes%20the%20original%20system%20of%20the%20selection%20of%20VCs%20through%20a%20neutral%20Selection%20Committee%20and%20gives%20exclusive%20power%20to%20the%20state%20government%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20top%20appointments%20in%20the%20universities.%20The%20government%20has%20similar%20proposals%20to%20amend%20other%20Acts%20of%20the%20state%20to%20bring%20democratic%20(political)%20influences%20by%20nominating%20MLAs%20in%20the%20governing%20bodies%20of%20its%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Funiversities-future-ruins-excellence%5C%22%3EIn%20Central%20Universities%2C%20the%20Future%20Will%20Now%20Be%20Built%20on%20the%20Ruins%20of%20Excellence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHimachal%20is%2C%20however%2C%20not%20the%20first%20state%20that%20has%20tried%20to%20diminish%20the%20autonomy%20of%20state%20universities.%20The%20first%20state%20was%20the%20Janata%20Party%20government%20of%20Gujarat%20which%20tried%20to%20control%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20universities%20by%20making%20the%20post%20of%20VC%20a%20political%20one.%20It%20amended%20the%20Gujarat%20University%20Act%2C%201949%20in%201978.%20Subsequently%2C%20there%20are%20many%20states%2C%20including%20Telangana%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20have%20followed%20similar%20policies.%20Recently%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20amended%20its%20two%20statutes%20in%202022%20to%20establish%20political%20control%20over%20the%20appointments%20of%20VCs%20in%20its%2013%20state%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInfluence%20of%20party%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20two%20years%20before%20the%20Gujarat%20amendment%2C%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20in%201976%20brought%20the%2042nd%20Amendment%20to%20the%20constitution%20and%20reconstituted%20the%20entire%20scheme%20of%20education%20under%20the%20Indian%20federal%20constitutional%20setup.%20In%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20post-colonial%20India%2C%20all%20educational%20institutions%2C%20except%20the%20existing%20three%20central%20universities%20such%20as%20Delhi%20University%2C%20Banaras%20Hindu%20University%2C%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%2C%20and%20a%20few%20central%20educational%20institutions%2C%20were%20schematised%20to%20be%20managed%20by%20the%20state%20governments.%20The%20government%20or%20parliament%20of%20India%20had%20only%20the%20power%20of%20coordination%20and%20maintenance%20of%20standards%20with%20respect%20to%20higher%20education.%20The%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%2C%20All%20India%20Council%20for%20Technical%20Education%20(AICTE)%2C%20Medical%20Council%20of%20India%20(MCI)%2C%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%20(BCI)%2C%20and%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%2C%20etc.%2C%20are%20the%20central%20agencies%20for%20coordinating%20and%20ensuring%20the%20minimum%20standard%20of%20education%20to%20be%20maintained%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2FJNU2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22On%20the%20JNU%20campus.%20Source%3A%20JNU%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2FJNU2.jpg%20960w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2FJNU2-300x198.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-21473%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22635%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20JNU%20campus.%20Source%3A%20JNU%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2042nd%20Amendment%20transferred%20the%20subject%20of%20%E2%80%98education%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20exclusive%20ambit%20of%20states%20(State%20List)%20to%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20where%20both%20the%20Centre%20and%20states%20can%20make%20laws%20on%20the%20same%20subject%20matter.%20But%2C%20in%20case%20of%20conflict%2C%20the%20Central%20legislation%20has%20primacy%20by%20virtue%20of%20Article%20254%20(rule%20of%20repugnancy)%20of%20the%20constitution.%20This%20new%20constitutional%20scheme%20has%20failed%20to%20establish%20a%20minimum%20standard%20for%20the%20administration%20of%20educational%20institutions%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETeaching%20is%20never%20a%20neutral%20act.%20All%20education%20is%20political%20(Paulo%20Friere%2C%201968).%20Paulo%20was%20talking%20about%20the%20methods%20of%20pedagogy.%20But%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20the%20education%20system%20is%20caught%20up%20in%20the%20power%20politics%20of%20political%20parties.%20As%20far%20as%20the%20education%20system%20is%20concerned%2C%20neither%20democratic%20politics%20nor%20constitutional%20federalism%20has%20served%20well%20in%20India.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20practical%20logic%20of%20party%20politics%20and%20shifting%20schemes%20of%20federalism%20have%20worked%20against%20the%20cause%20of%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20school%20education%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021A%20of%20the%20constitution%20for%20every%20child%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%206-14%20years.%20Notably%2C%20Article%2026%20of%20the%20Universal%20Declaration%20of%20Human%20Rights%2C%201948%20declares%20the%20right%20to%20education%20a%20human%20right.%20Its%20language%20expresses%20the%20morality%20of%20aspiration%20to%20ensure%20elementary%20education%20is%20free%20and%20compulsory%20and%20higher%20or%20technical%20education%20accessible%20to%20all%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20merit.%20These%20normative%20enunciations%20mean%20little%20to%20the%20Indian%20policymakers%20who%20have%20increasingly%20used%20the%20system%20of%20school%20and%20higher%20education%20as%20a%20means%20of%20party%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20vice-chancellor%20of%20a%20university%20is%20the%20leader%20of%20that%20institution%20whose%20visions%20and%20actions%20lead%20the%20university%20in%20a%20certain%20direction.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20post%20of%20vice-chancellor%20should%20be%20held%20by%20an%20academician%20of%20profound%20intellect%20and%20highest%20integrity.%20The%20moment%20this%20post%20is%20made%20into%20political%20largesse%2C%20by%20any%20political%20party%20in%20power%2C%20its%20independence%20is%20compromised.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20both%20in%20central%20universities%20and%20national%20institutions%20of%20importance%20too%2C%20political%20parties%20have%20been%20playing%20a%20decisive%20role.%20Teachers%20of%20colleges%20or%20degree%20colleges%20have%20been%20appointed%20to%20the%20post%20of%20vice-chancellor%20frequently.%20People%20such%20as%20careerists%20from%20private%20universities%20are%20rewarded%20with%20the%20post%20of%20vice-chancellor%20or%20registrar%20due%20to%20their%20connection%20with%20the%20political%20party%20in%20power.%20Parties%20do%20it%2C%20chiefly%2C%20to%20strengthen%20their%20cadre%20base%20by%20way%20of%20gifts%20of%20state%20largess.%20Immediately%2C%20the%20education%20system%20falls%20victim%20to%20the%20party-centric%20political%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fthe-virus-of-delegated-authoritarianism-or-why-we-mustnt-ignore-jnu-v-cs-evasions%5C%22%3EThe%20Virus%20of%20Delegated%20Authoritarianism%2C%20or%20Why%20We%20Mustn%E2%80%99t%20Ignore%20JNU%20V-C%E2%80%99s%20Evasions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPublic%20reason%20and%20electoral%20democracy%20are%20concepts%20that%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20essence.%20The%20government%20of%20the%20day%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20so-called%20custodian%20of%20public%20reason.%20However%2C%20neither%20public%20reason%20nor%20democracy%20can%20be%20conducive%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20knowledge%20and%20education.%20Thus%2C%20traditionally%2C%20universities%20have%20been%20regarded%20to%20be%20autonomous%20spaces%3B%20free%20from%20not%20only%20unrestricted%20governmental%20control%20but%20also%20from%20the%20coercive%20sentiments%20and%20opinions%20relating%20to%20morality%20and%20cultural%20norms%20emanating%20from%20the%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20cadres%20of%20the%20political%20parties%20are%20the%20chief%20instruments%20for%20exercising%20social%2C%20political%2C%20and%20legal%20coercion%20in%20the%20education%20system.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20%E2%80%98guest%20teachers%E2%80%99%20without%20any%20merit-based%20examination%20has%20already%20done%20irreparable%20damage%20to%20government%20schools.%20Every%20government%20gives%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20appointment%20of%20guest%20teachers%20to%20its%20party%20workers.%20Later%20on%2C%20through%20legal%20battles%20in%20the%20courts%2C%20the%20permanency%20of%20the%20job%20is%20secured%20by%20the%20guest%20teachers%20and%20the%20question%20of%20merit%20disappears%20forever.%20A%20similar%20pattern%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Bihar%2C%20among%20others%20under%20the%20Shiksha%20Mitra%20Scheme.%20The%20scheme%20is%20notorious%20as%20%3Cem%3EShiksha%20Shatru%3C%2Fem%3E%20(enemy%20of%20school%20education).%20Not%20unexpectedly%2C%20private%20schools%20with%20poor%20quality%20have%20been%20mushrooming%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20for%20the%20last%20two%20decades.%20Almost%20every%20village%2C%20%3Cem%3EKasba%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20town%20has%20some%20sort%20of%20private%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20consideration%20for%20academic%20standards%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20respect%20to%20the%20system%20of%20university%2C%20it%20should%20be%20clearly%20understood%20that%20the%20universities%20must%20be%20governed%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cacademic%20reason%E2%80%9D%20primarily.%20Academic%20reason%20comes%20with%20commitment%2C%20devotion%2C%20and%20lifelong%20dedication%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20knowledge%2C%20truth%2C%20and%20good%20academic%20accomplishments%20but%20not%20by%20political%20interference.%20If%20the%20teachers%20of%20universities%20are%20appointed%20due%20to%20political%20allegiance%20rather%20than%20academic%20merit%20then%20what%20can%20one%20expect%20from%20Indian%20universities%20with%20respect%20to%20academic%20excellence%3F%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20state%20of%20affairs%20is%20visible%20in%20all%20prominent%20universities%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20it%20is%20believed%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20interferes%20in%20the%20governance%20of%20state%20universities%20through%20the%20agency%20of%20governors.%20In%20reaction%2C%20the%20states%20are%20resorting%20to%20amendments%20in%20their%20laws.%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20the%20autonomy%20of%20universities%20and%20academic%20standards%20which%20suffer.%20The%20contemporary%20systems%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20vice-chancellor%20in%20Indian%20universities%20are%20not%20governed%20by%20academic%20reason%20rather%20it%20is%20determined%20by%20the%20political%20expediency%20of%20the%20party%20in%20power.%20Teaching%2C%20learning%2C%20and%20administration%20of%20the%20institution%20are%20affected%20by%20the%20policies%20and%20preferences%20of%20the%20vice-chancellor%20who%20needs%20to%20please%20%E2%80%93%20in%20a%20give-and-take%20manner%20%E2%80%93%20the%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20fate%20of%20leadership%20in%20higher%20educational%20institutions%20may%20be%20understood%20by%20asking%20a%20few%20conjectural%20questions.%20A%20student%20may%20simply%20ask%20herself%20how%20many%20research%20articles%20her%20vice-chancellor%2Fdirector%20has%20written%20which%20ought%20to%20be%20taught%20and%20read%20in%20her%20Master%E2%80%99s%20Course.%20Has%20her%20head%20of%20the%20institution%20produced%20academic%20books%20that%20can%20be%20prescribed%20as%20mandatory%20reference%20material%20in%20her%20post-graduation%20course%3F%20How%20many%20works%20of%20such%20head%2Fleader%20are%20part%20of%20reference%20courses%20in%20the%20top%201%2C000%20universities%20of%20the%20world%3F%20And%20so%20on.%20Most%20of%20the%20vice-chancellors%20on%20these%20parameters%20do%20not%20have%20to%20their%20credit%20significant%20academic%20contributions.%20But%20their%20political%20background%20and%20efficacious%20lobbying%20help%20them%20to%20reach%20the%20top%20posts%20in%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWay%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDemocracy%20has%20both%20emancipatory%20as%20well%20as%20repressive%20and%20regressive%20potential.%20Thus%2C%20there%20are%20politics%20of%20justice%2C%20fairness%2C%20liberation%2C%20and%20excellence.%20There%20are%20also%20politics%20of%20subjugation%2C%20domination%2C%20deprivation%2C%20and%20regression.%20The%20education%20system%20in%20India%20is%20suffering%20from%20the%20malaise%20of%20the%20latter%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20corrected%20urgently%20to%20revive%20the%20spirit%20of%20education%20as%20a%20process%20of%20contemplation%20and%20critical%20exploration.%20India%20needs%20Gandhian%20praxis%20of%20pragmatism%2C%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20humanism%2C%20and%20Tagore%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20aestheticism%20in%20the%20leadership%20of%20higher%20education%20to%20visualise%20the%20renaissance%20of%20education%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20that%20a%20system%20of%20academic%20audit%20is%20devised%20and%20every%20candidate%20for%20the%20top%20positions%20of%20leadership%20in%20universities%20is%20assessed%20accordingly.%20The%20system%20of%20assessment%20may%20be%20operationalised%20by%20a%20neutral%20selection%20or%20screening%20committee%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20publicised%20academic%20audit%20reports%20amongst%20the%20professors%2C%20scholars%2C%20and%20students%20where%20the%20idea%20of%20academic%20reason%20can%20have%20a%20sufficient%20role%20to%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr.%20Chanchal%20Kumar%20Singh%2C%20Professor%20of%20Law%2C%20and%20Director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Comparative%20Public%20Law%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20National%20Law%20University%20(HPNLU)%2C%20Shimla.%20Dr.%20Mritunjay%20Kumar%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Coordinator%2C%20Centre%20for%20Comparative%20Public%20Law%2C%20HPNLU%2C%20Shimla.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697869857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%